verses.text_plain: In the Lord put I my trust: how say ye to my soul, Flee as a bird to your mountain?
verses.verse_html: 1In the Lord put I my trust: how say ye to my soul, Flee as a bird to your mountain?

verses.text_plain: For, lo, the wicked bend their bow, they make ready their arrow upon the string, that they may privily shoot at the upright in heart.
verses.verse_html:
2For, lo, the wicked bend their bow, they make ready their arrow upon the string, that they may privily shoot at the upright in heart. ▼
▼ privily: Heb. in darkness

footnotes.body_html: ▼ privily: Heb. in darkness

verses.text_plain: If the foundations be destroyed, what can the righteous do?
verses.verse_html: 3If the foundations be destroyed, what can the righteous do?

verses.text_plain: The Lord is in his holy temple, the Lord’s throne is in heaven: his eyes behold, his eyelids try, the children of men.
verses.verse_html: 4The Lord is in his holy temple, the Lord’s throne is in heaven: his eyes behold, his eyelids try, the children of men.

verses.text_plain: The Lord trieth the righteous: but the wicked and him that loveth violence his soul hateth.
verses.verse_html: 5The Lord trieth the righteous: but the wicked and him that loveth violence his soul hateth.

verses.text_plain: Upon the wicked he shall rain snares, fire and brimstone, and an horrible tempest: this shall be the portion of their cup.
verses.verse_html:
6Upon the wicked he shall rain snares, fire and brimstone, and an horrible tempest: this shall be the portion of their cup. ▼
▼ an horrible…: or, a burning tempest

footnotes.body_text: ▼ an horrible…: or, a burning tempest
footnotes.body_html: ▼ an horrible…: or, a burning tempest

verses.text_plain: For the righteous Lord loveth righteousness; his countenance doth behold the upright.
verses.verse_html: 7For the righteous Lord loveth righteousness; his countenance doth behold the upright.
